# .trivyignore — Accepted CVE exceptions for trivy image scanning
#
# Format:
#   <CVE-ID>  # <base-image>: <rationale> | Review by: <YYYY-MM-DD>
#
# Policy:
#   - Every entry MUST include: CVE ID, affected image, rationale, and a review date.
#   - Additions require a PR review from at least one other engineer.
#   - Review dates should be set no further than 90 days from acceptance.
#   - Remove entries once an upstream fix is available and the base image is updated.
#
# Example (do not uncomment unless this CVE has been evaluated):
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX  # python:3.14-slim: No fix available upstream; only exploitable
#                   # via direct filesystem access not possible in our runtime config.
#                   # Review by: 2026-06-08
